* Iron Raptor knew that he was going to try and stop her now, and just as 
Prowl was about to dig his talons into her she was getting ready to kick 
back and get him away.
But instead, when she expected to feel him grab her she heard a few frantic 
flapps of wings, a sickening crack, a few more cracks which were branches of 
the forest she had just entered and another bonysounding snap.

She looked back over her shoulder as she ran to look for Prowl, but the 
forst was to dense to see anything in it other then the bushes and tree.
Her eyes scanned the area...but a little accident of her own was just about 
to happen!
Not looking where she was going she ran smack dab right into a large tree 
trunk, her shoulder hit first and the trunk shattered from the impact.
Brought to a dead stop she staggered back for a few steps before she simply 
sat down hard on her rear, sitting there stunned for a few moments as she 
just watched the tree creek and goran as it slowly fell to the ground, 
taking a few others with it.

But then she simply shook her hed and looked down at her shoulder, a little 
yellow mech-fluid leeking from it. Nothing seriouse.
Iron Raptor got to herfeet and then raised to her hind legs, taking the 
weight off her shoulder which was already damaged.
She looked around the new clearing for a moment before turning back, knowing 
that Prowl would have to be there somewhere.

It wasn't long before she finally found him, just freshly fallen from the 
trees above...since all the branches were broken and hanging.
He must have ran into a branch as he swooped down on her, then went through 
everything else until he finally landed on his stomach on the forest floor.
Iron Raptor sighed and walked up to him, seeing his wing which looked to be 
broken. Worry on her features.*

" Prowl?"


He
>transforms and falls to the ground, landing on his stomach as he hits
>several more branches.
